title: Senators Probe TikTok's Executive Transfers From ByteDance
description: The senators want information about TikTok’s ties to its parent, including whether it disclosed recent personnel moves to the U.S. government.

title: Intel to Spin Off Programmable Solutions Group
description: Chip maker says separate group will go public in coming years.

title: Amazon Used Secret 'Project Nessie' Algorithm to Raise Prices
description: Amazon.com used an algorithm code-named “Project Nessie” to test how much it could raise prices in a way that competitors would follow, according to redacted portions of the FTC’s monopoly lawsuit.

title: Meta Floats Charging $14 a Month for Ad-Free Instagram
description: European users would have the option to pay a fee or agree to personalized ads, according to the company’s pitch to regulators.
